    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      66.03,
      167.63,
      307.54,
      194.7
    ],
    "text": "BE it enacted by the Parliament of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka as follows: -",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      66.03,
      208.39,
      307.3,
      234.23
    ],
    "text": "1. This Act may be cited as the Parliamentary Pensions (Repeal) Act, No. 5 of 2026.",
    "fonts": [
      "MinionPro-Bold",
      "MinionPro-Regular"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      66.03,
      235.23,
      307.31,
      273.23
    ],
    "text": "2. The Parliamentary Pensions Law, No. 1 of 1977 is hereby repealed.",
    "fonts": [
      "MinionPro-Bold",
      "MinionPro-Regular",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      66.03,
      274.23,
      307.55,
      396.5
    ],
    "text": "3. For the avoidance of doubt, it is hereby declared that any person who is entitled to receive a pension in terms of the provisions of the Parliamentary Pensions Law, No. 1 of 1977, section 9 of Act, No. 1 of 1982 or section 9 of Act, No. 47 of 1990, and is in receipt of a pension under the aforesaid provisions preceding the date of commencement of this Act, shall, on and after the date of commencement of this Act, cease to receive such pension.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      66.03,
      398.03,
      307.55,
      438.7
    ],
    "text": "4. In the event of any inconsistency between the Sinhala and Tamil texts of this Act, the Sinhala text shall prevail.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
